hire, and perhaps also from Downham, Northumberland, and <i>Downholme</i>, North Yorkshire, though no evidence has been found for these. The names from Lancashire and Northumberland arise from Old English <i>dūn</i>, dative plural <i>dūnum</i> ‘(at) the hills’, while the others come from Old English <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’ + <i>hām</i> ‘homestead’.","Altered form of English   Dunham  ."]},{"name":"Dunnam","meanings":["English: variant of   Dunham  ."]},{"name":"Donham","meanings":["English: variant of   Dunham  ."]}]},{"name":"Rychert","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Willi, Alois, Alphons, Bernhard, Erhard, Erwin, Gerhard, Gerhardt, Hermann, Kurt, Monika.","variant of   Richer   or   Richard  .","altered form of   Reichert  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Richer","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Armand, Fernand, Herve, Laurent, Marcel, Aurele, Donat, Elphege, Emile, Flore, Gilles.","English (East Anglia), French, and German: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful)’ + <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’. The name was introduced into England by the Normans in the form <i>Rich(i)er</i>, <i>Ricier</i>, but was largely absorbed by the much more common   Richard  .","Altered form of French <b>Héricher</b>: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Harigari</i>, composed of the elements <i>hari</i> ‘army’ and <i>gari</i> (from <i>garwa</i>) ‘ready, eager’ or <i>gari</i> ‘spear’, or a variant of <b>Hérissé</b>, a nickname for someone with spiky hair, from the adjective <i>hérissé</i>, a derivative of the verb <i>se hérisser</i> ‘to stand on end’."]},{"name":"Ritzert","meanings":["German: variant of   Richert  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Rychert Dunham was born on 14 February 1294, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Joscelin Dinham, was 11291 and his mother, Margaret Hydon, was 23. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Beneditcia Folsgamble. He died on 30 March 1330, in his hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"14 February 1294–30 March 1330":"14. veebruar 1294–30. märts 1330","1294–1330":"1294–1330","1295–1332":"1295–1332","1298–1342":"1298–1342","1298–1379":"1298–1379","1318–1409":"1318–1409","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1329–Female":"1329–Surnud","–1314":"–1314","1275–1301":"1275–1301","1272–1357":"1272–1357","30 March 1301":"30. märts 1301","9 SEP 1329":"9. september 1329","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","14 February 1294":"14. veebruar 1294","1295":"1295","1272":"1272","1294":"1294","17 JUN 1320":"17. juuni 1320","1314":"1314","1357":"1357","1379":"1379","1301":"1301","about 1314":"umbes 1314","1332":"1332","1320":"1320","1342":"1342","1298":"1298","30 March 1330":"30. märts 1330","8 Jan 1318":"8. jaanuar 1318","1409":"1409","1329":"1329","1318":"1318",",,Devon,England":"Devon, England","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"14 February 1294–30 March 1330":"14. helmikuuta 1294–30. maaliskuuta 1330","1294–1330":"1294–1330","1295–1332":"1295–1332","1298–1342":"1298–1342","1298–1379":"1298–1379","1318–1409":"1318–1409","1320–Female":"1320–Kuollut","1329–Female":"1329–Kuollut","–1314":"–1314","1275–1301":"1275–1301","1272–1357":"1272–1357","30 March 1301":"30. maaliskuuta 1301","9 SEP 1329":"9. syyskuuta 1329","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","14 February 1294":"14. helmikuuta 1294","1295":"1295","1272":"1272","1294":"1294","17 JUN 1320":"17. kesäkuuta 1320","1314":"1314","1357":"1357","1379":"1379","1301":"1301","about 1314":"noin 1314","1332":"1332","1320":"1320","1342":"1342","1298":"1298","30 March 1330":"30. maaliskuuta 1330","8 Jan 1318":"8. tammikuuta 1318","1409":"1409","1329":"1329","1318":"1318",",,Devon,England":"Devon, England","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"14 February 1294–30 March 1330":"14 février 1294–30 mars 1330","1294–1330":"1294–1